  "script": "A raccoon? In a jar? Animal control in Dedham, Massachusetts got a call about a young raccoon running around with a glass jar over its head, rapidly running out of air. Officers arrived, grabbed the raccoon, and after a few quick twists and pulls, got the jar off. They had CPR compressions ready. A wildlife rehabilitator was on standby. The raccoon had gone critical — its eyes were barely moving when they arrived. Jar off. A few dizzy stumbles. Then it righted itself, crawled through a fence slat, and climbed straight to the top of a wooden swing set. The 5-year-old kid who lived there watched the whole thing. Everyone confirmed it was totally fine. So does the raccoon know it almost didn't make it?",
